  "business_context": "Recurring Gift records are the schedule and parent for donations that repeat on a cadence. They define the amount per installment, the frequency (monthly, quarterly, annually, custom), the start date, the end condition (open-ended versus fixed number of installments), and the payment method. Each scheduled installment generates a child Donation record at the appropriate date. Recurring giving is one of the most-watched metrics in modern fundraising — sustaining donors (those who give monthly or quarterly) typically have multi-year retention rates 5-10x higher than one-time donors, so growing the recurring base is a strategic priority for most organizations. Modeling varies: NPSP uses Recurring Donation (npe03__Recurring_Donation__c) as a separate object that auto-generates Opportunity installment records; CiviCRM uses ContributionRecur with the same parent-child pattern; Bloomerang uses RecurringDonation; B2B systems without nonprofit overlays don't have this concept and require custom build-out. When interviewing clients, surface \"Recurring Gift\" by asking whether they accept recurring donations, whether they need to track scheduled versus actual giving, whether they need failed-payment retry workflows, and whether they need cadence-change tracking (donor increases monthly amount; donor pauses; donor cancels).",
  "catalog_id": "recurring-gift",
